The Judiciary has condemned attacks against judicial officers by government officials. In a meeting chaired by Chief Justice David Maraga, the Judicial Service Commission said they will not sit back and watch politicians and State officers engage in public lynching of judges.&ldquo;In particular, JSC expressed its outrage at the emerging trend where State officials and other parties have engaged in open manifestation of disrespect to the courts and judicial process,&rdquo; said Chief Registrar of Judiciary Anne Amadi. &nbsp;The commission singled out National Assembly Leader of Majority Aden Duale for attacking Justice George Odunga over a court matter he was handling in December last year. -Paul Ogemba